<subSubSection lastPageId="76" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1436,1974,2035]" lastBlockId="76.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="76" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1974,1999]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Easily distinguished from most known congeners by armature of male chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1381,1974,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES306–311" captionStartId="76.[151,264,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[153,1430,301,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@76.[151,1436,301,1914]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES306–311. Mesabolivaramadoi sp.n. (ZFMKAr 19147).306–307.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 308–309.Tip of leftprocursus,prolateral and dorsalviews.310–311.Male chelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.Scale lines:0.5 (306–307, 310–311), 0.2 (308–309)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202595/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Figs 310–311</figureCitation>
; two pairs of frontal apophyses), tip of procursus (
<figureCitation box="[665,825,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURES306–311" captionStartId="76.[151,264,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[153,1430,301,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@76.[151,1436,301,1914]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES306–311. Mesabolivaramadoi sp.n. (ZFMKAr 19147).306–307.Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 308–309.Tip of leftprocursus,prolateral and dorsalviews.310–311.Male chelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.Scale lines:0.5 (306–307, 310–311), 0.2 (308–309)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202595/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Figs 308–309</figureCitation>
; distinctive shape of prolateral process), and shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[280,440,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 312–314" captionStartId="77.[151,264,898,920]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,185,881]" captionTargetId="figure@77.[151,1436,175,894]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 312–314. Mesabolivar amadoi sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 19148). 312–313. Epigynum, ventral and lateral views. 314. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines:0.3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202597/files/figure.png" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Figs 312–313</figureCitation>
; anterior plate with large central whitish depression and pair of apophyses); from most similar known species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2015" box="[419,528,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonita">
<emphasis box="[419,528,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">M. bonita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by apophyses on epigynum (absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2015" box="[981,1091,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonita">
<emphasis box="[981,1091,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">M. bonita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by positions and sizes of male cheliceral apophyses (proximal apophyses smaller; distal apophyses in more proximal position).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
